The significance of non-inpatient and skilled nursing services also has increased, although it varies by hospital
location (see Table 1-4). In 1985 about 40 percent of rural community hospitals reported having any organized
outpatient service; by 1992, more than 84 percent had this capability. While 17 percent of rural hospitals surveyed
