 An adjustment of zero percentage points to correct for past forecast errors;
 An adjustment of zero percentage points to reflect changes in financing costs;
 A positive adjustment of 0.9 percentage points for scientific and technological advances;
 A negative adjustment of 0.7 percentage points to encourage hospital productivity; and
 A net adjustment for zero percentage points for case-mix change.
The Commission's recommendations would result in a 3.6 percent increase in the Federal capital payment rate for both
urban and rural hospitals.
ProPAC believes the capital update should be for future capital purchases. It is designed to provide Medicare capital
